      "page_number": 6
    }
  },
  {
    "element_id": "cfd0f8d2f101fdfebc70eee3c3c7f5f7",
    "text": "Senior Commissioner’s Representatives Roles in Management of IRS Field and Headquarters Offices.",
    "type": "ListItem",
    "metadata": {
      "filename": "zips/irm10-006-006--2022-03-18.pdf",
      "page_number": 6
    }
  },
  {
    "element_id": "d70ab836ee54b89e2ee4966ab02ff47a",
    "text": "Facilities Management and Security Services (FMSS) will:",
    "type": "NarrativeText",
    "metadata": {
      "filename": "zips/irm10-006-006--2022-03-18.pdf",
      "page_number": 6
    }
  },
  {
    "element_id": "b42ff9d5fa8344ce8ef529b337248a35",
    "text": "a. Update Situational Awareness Management Center (SAMC) as appropri",
    "type": "ListItem",
    "metadata": {
      "filename": "zips/irm10-006-006--2022-03-18.pdf",
      "page_number": 6
    }
  },
  {
    "element_id": "147929494b559ac2c2fb57cbc60aedea",
    "text": "ate; b. Direct control and restrictions to IRS space as appropriate; c. Identify and manage cleaning and supply of Personal Protective Equipment (PPE) as recommended by Center for Disease Control (CDC) guidance.",
    "type": "ListItem",
    "metadata": {
      "filename": "zips/irm10-006-006--2022-03-18.pdf",
      "page_number": 6
    }
  },
  {
    "element_id": "75438548ac5b9addddf89f586ca93fec",
    "text": "Within the IRS, Infectious Disease Reporting Procedures and providing reports to other agencies; Work Related Travel; Services covered under relevant contracts.",
    "type": "ListItem",
    "metadata": {
      "filename": "zips/irm10-006-006--2022-03-18.pdf",
      "page_number": 6
    }
  },
  {
    "element_id": "8977538b9eae8177355e4a38437108b3",
    "text": "Other information which may be required:",
    "type": "NarrativeText",
    "metadata": {
      "filename": "zips/irm10-006-006--2022-03-18.pdf",
      "page_number": 7
    }
  },
  {
    "element_id": "7979c3d785a8dfb04845b0b5e6f521c9",
    "text": "The Information Technology Office is required to provide updates to ANNEX B: Pandemic Inﬂuenza – ITs’ Strategy for Preparedness.",
    "type": "NarrativeText",
    "metadata": {
      "filename": "zips/irm10-006-006--2022-03-18.pdf",
      "page_number": 7
    }
  },
  {
    "element_id": "33feac0fdcbc2ce053e6d97afa5f298f",
    "text": "a. Contingency Planning; b. Operations; c. Telework; d. Personnel; e. IT Security; f. Supplies and Services. (",
    "type": "ListItem",
    "metadata": {
      "filename": "zips/irm10-006-006--2022-03-18.pdf",
      "page_number": 7
    }
  },
  {
    "element_id": "fa2777b615c42e8c80f0483b6f1b9f00",
    "text": ") Essential Functions: As with all continuity plans, Federal Continuity Directives (FCD)",
    "type": "ListItem",
    "metadata": {
      "filename": "zips/irm10-006-006--2022-03-18.pdf",
      "page_number": 7
    }
  },
  {
    "element_id": "6201111b83a0cb5b0922cb37cc442b9a",
    "text": "and",
    "type": "ListItem",
    "metadata": {
      "filename": "zips/irm10-006-006--2022-03-18.pdf",
      "page_number": 7
    }
  },
  {
    "element_id": "e02159cd67a80dc267bc207527c15997",
    "text": "guide the identiﬁcation of essential functions. Agency pandemic inﬂuenza plans should ensure continuity of Mission Essential Functions (MEFs) and Essential Supporting Activities (ESAs) throughout a pandemic. (",
    "type": "ListItem",
    "metadata": {
      "filename": "zips/irm10-006-006--2022-03-18.pdf",
      "page_number": 7
    }
  },
  {
    "element_id": "f78719cb1923df63309def66768c2cd7",
    "text": ") Due to the extended duration of a pandemic, essential functions addressed within pandemic plans would also include functions that cannot be deferred",
    "type": "ListItem",
    "metadata": {
      "filename": "zips/irm10-006-006--2022-03-18.pdf",
      "page_number": 7
    }
  },
  {
    "element_id": "73bb33ac762a003be68114cf8370c6bb",
    "text": "weeks or more without impact to an agency’s mission. (",
    "type": "ListItem",
    "metadata": {
      "filename": "zips/irm10-006-006--2022-03-18.pdf",
      "page_number": 7
    }
  },
  {
    "element_id": "c1f93631f900b31f89e5884b4787f7a1",
    "text": ") In addition, agency plans may address non-essential functions that could be deferred, but can be continued through Telework or otherwise modiﬁed opera- tionally to keep employee(s) from being at risk while performing those functions (as with all essential functions). (",
    "type": "ListItem",
    "metadata": {
      "filename": "zips/irm10-006-006--2022-03-18.pdf",
      "page_number": 7
    }
  },
  {
    "element_id": "d8ea706f463302fa08ddad4288901d23",
    "text": ") The functions (and supporting services) addressed within pandemic planning may be performed by Federal agency employees or contractors. (",
    "type": "ListItem",
    "metadata": {
      "filename": "zips/irm10-006-006--2022-03-18.pdf",
      "page_number": 7
    }
  },
  {
    "element_id": "2a8d747615527c1f88a169ace1da2c45",
    "text": ") There are no pre-determined reports for Pandemics. (",
    "type": "ListItem",
    "metadata": {
      "filename": "zips/irm10-006-006--2022-03-18.pdf",
      "page_number": 7
    }
  },
  {
    "element_id": "72f66ded46a6cbdf5f053600c4215702",
    "text": ") During a Pandemic event, status reports will be submitted to the IRS Commis- sioner and the Department of the Treasury (Treasury) on a schedule determined at that time. (",
    "type": "ListItem",
    "metadata": {
      "filename": "zips/irm10-006-006--2022-03-18.pdf",
      "page_number": 7
    }
  },
  {
    "element_id": "ec5f87c41651be9fc4388adadc850a49",
    "text": ") For further information see section",
    "type": "ListItem",
    "metadata": {
      "filename": "zips/irm10-006-006--2022-03-18.pdf",
      "page_number": 7
    }
  },
  {
    "element_id": "7cd439430ad939bc3043797cf71e2681",
    "text": "of this IRM Other Pandemic Reporting. (",
    "type": "ListItem",
    "metadata": {
      "filename": "zips/irm10-006-006--2022-03-18.pdf",
      "page_number": 7
    }
  },
  {
    "element_id": "e62fbf3dd26671e01c41a35da1a53039",
    "text": ") See IRM",
    "type": "ListItem",
    "metadata": {
      "filename": "zips/irm10-006-006--2022-03-18.pdf",
      "page_number": 7
    }
  },
  {
    "element_id": "a7feb0f10daf654b59a112662e02bfb6",
    "text": "Introduction to Continuity Planning .",
    "type": "ListItem",
    "metadata": {
      "filename": "zips/irm10-006-006--2022-03-18.pdf",
      "page_number": 7
    }
  },
  {
    "element_id": "3ded25068a9151afe178bc6316882bd7",
    "text": "Essential Functions: As with all continuity plans, Federal Continuity Directives (FCD) 1 and 2 guide the identiﬁcation of essential functions. Agency pandemic inﬂuenza plans should ensure continuity of Mission Essential Functions (MEFs) and Essential Supporting Activities (ESAs) throughout a pandemic.",
    "type": "NarrativeText",
    "metadata": {
      "filename": "zips/irm10-006-006--2022-03-18.pdf",
      "page_number": 7
    }
  },
  {
    "element_id": "04e3877ca7aac41dd69cad047fe12f6b",
    "text": "The functions (and supporting services) addressed within pandemic planning may be performed by Federal agency employees or contractors.",
    "type": "NarrativeText",
    "metadata": {
      "filename": "zips/irm10-006-006--2022-03-18.pdf",
      "page_number": 7
    }
  },
  {
    "element_id": "db314efa28f3f33d1c3292fefab782b3",
    "text": "See IRM 10.6.1 Introduction to Continuity Planning for general acronyms.",
    "type": "NarrativeText",
    "metadata": {
      "filename": "zips/irm10-006-006--2022-03-18.pdf",
      "page_number": 8
    }
  },
  {
    "element_id": "b99b381dd79a18f85e5b8f31fd1802ad",
    "text": "The Pandemic Plan must contain the information necessary for IRS leadership to maintain operations during a signiﬁcant reduction in staffing due to illness.",
    "type": "NarrativeText",
    "metadata": {
      "filename": "zips/irm10-006-006--2022-03-18.pdf",
      "page_number": 8
    }
  },
  {
    "element_id": "e485ad1696e5b412922e90ab57540334",
    "text": "Note: These Pandemic Plan requirements overlap but do not completely track the requirements for a Continuity Plan.",
    "type": "NarrativeText",
    "metadata": {
      "filename": "zips/irm10-006-006--2022-03-18.pdf",
      "page_number": 8
    }
  },
  {
    "element_id": "32ebb1abcc1c601ceb9c4e3c4faba0ca",
    "text": "(",
    "type": "ListItem",
    "metadata": {
      "filename": "zips/irm10-006-006--2022-03-18.pdf",
      "page_number": 8
    }
  },
  {
    "element_id": "3532f731a8efc3cdc655639557eedbcf",
    "text": ") Annex A - IRS Pandemic Decision Matrix - This is a high level tool for use by IRS decision makers and BU managers to guide pandemic planning, prepared- ness, and response activities. It provides a summary list of response actions and considerations that support meeting the objectives identiﬁed in the IRS Pandemic Plan. It also identiﬁes factors that may limit the implementation of response actions. Coordinated by SCR-CO:CO.",
